<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Teen's grandmother files suit one year after shooting  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- The grandmother of Aquan Salmon has filed
a federal lawsuit over the fatal shooting of the black teen-ager by
a white Hartford police officer.
</P>
<P>
   The lawsuit, filed by Norma Watts in U.S. District Court in
Hartford, claims Officer Robert C. Allan violated the 14-year-old's
civil rights when he shot him to death on April 13, 1999.
</P>
<P>
   The lawsuit seeks unspecified monetary damages, Joseph Moniz,
Watts' attorney, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ''The main goal is to keep this from happening again to anyone
else,'' he said. ''They're seeking to get conditions within the
city to ensure that this won't happen again.''
</P>
<P>
   The lawsuit seeks enforcement of a 1973 consent decree on the
use of force by Hartford police. Moniz claims the higher standards
and training policies mandated after the city was sued by the
community group La Casa, were ignored in the Salmon shooting.
</P>
<P>
   ''Had they been followed, this death would not have occurred,''
Moniz said.
</P>
<P>
   La Casa, a coalition of black and Hispanic groups, filed a
motion claiming the city had reneged on the consent decree after
Salmon's death. The group dropped its lawsuit after the city vowed
to revive a review board to investigate police shootings.
</P>
<P>
   Watts' lawsuit names the city of Hartford as well as Allan.
</P>
<P>
   ''He is the product of a department that had certain problems,''
Moniz said.
</P>
<P>
   Allan shot Salmon early in the morning of April 13, 1999 after
several teen-agers, one carrying a lighter shaped like a gun, fled
from a car police had been chasing through the city's north end.
</P>
<P>
   Allan claimed Salmon appeared to be reaching for a weapon.
Special prosecutor, New London State's Attorney Kevin Kane, found
in February that the shooting was justified.
</P>
<P>
   According to his report, Salmon had reached toward his waistband
and was turning toward Allan when the officer fired one shot into
the left side of his back.
</P>
<P>
   Salmon and the other teens had been wanted for an attempted
mugging and pistol-whipping earlier in the night.
</P>
<P>
   Watts has said she believes Allan should be jailed for the
shooting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
