<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Drops Another 88; Dow Down 143  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 143
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold about a 3-1 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 88 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down 14 points.
</P>
<P>
   Today's inflation news is serving to scare away any remaining
week-kneed investors from the market.
</P>
<P>
   The Labor Department said consumer prices rose 0.7 percent in
March, while the core rate of inflation rose by its fastest pace in
five years.
</P>
<P>
   The news is seen as adding to the pressure on the Federal
Reserve to again hike interest rates next month.
</P>
<P>
   There is some earnings news for Wall Street to consider, with a
better-than-expected report from Sun Microsystems, and numbers from
Gateway that matched estimates.
