<DOCNO> APW20000414.0132 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 12:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton To Address College Grads  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will address the 2,000
graduating classes of the U.S. Coast Guard, Eastern Michigan
University and Carleton College.
</P>
<P>
   The president traditionally delivers commencement addresses to
one of the nation's military academies, one private school and one
public school.
</P>
<P>
   The White House announced Friday that Clinton will travel to
Ypsilanti, Mich., on April 30, to the Coast Guard Academy in New
London, Conn., on May 17 and to Carleton in Northfield, Minn., on
June 10.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Clinton spoke to the graduates at the Air Force
Academy, Grambling State University and the University of Chicago.
</P>
