<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Friday, April 14, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dow Sinks 521; Nasdaq Tumbles 295
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices plunged today, pulling the Dow
Jones industrials and Nasdaq composite index down hundreds of
points as investors responded to new inflation reports with furious
selling. Just before 3 p.m. EDT, the Dow was down 521.29 at
10,402.26. The blue-chip index is down about 11 percent from its
Jan. 14 record of 11,722.98. The Nasdaq tumbled as well. By
midafternoon, it was down 295.71 at 3,381.07. The Nasdaq already
had plunged 769 points, or 17 percent, in the first four days of
this week. The losses engulfed brokerage companies, many of which
saw their shares slide 10 percent or more. Transportation stocks
and technology stocks also took it on the chin.
</P>
