<HEADLINE> Internet company offering Hillary Clinton doormats  </HEADLINE>
With AM-NY--NY Senate
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Announcing that ''she's been a doormat,'' a
new Web site is offering the real thing emblazoned with a likeness
of Senate candidate Hillary Rodham Clinton and catchy phrases such
as ''I've always been a Yankee fan.''
</P>
<P>
   For $19.95, the site offers the ''Hillary Doormat'' which is
described as ''America's favorite place to wipe its political
feet.''
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is running for a Senate seat from New York against New
York City Mayor Rudolph Giuliani.
</P>
<P>
   A selection of ''Hillaryisms'' can be ordered on the doormats,
including ''It's all a vast Right Wing Conspiracy!'' and ''Read my
lips -- No New Interns!''
</P>
<P>
   The Web site's address is: hillarydoormat.com.
</P>
<P>
   The doormat-marketing company is headed by Jazz Perazic-Gipe, a
former college basketball star who played one season with the New
York Liberty of the Women's National Basketball Association.
</P>
<P>
   She told the New York Post that the idea came to her when she
was playing a pickup basketball game with friends. When talk turned
to the first lady, Perazic-Gipe blurted out, ''That woman's a
doormat,'' the Post reported.
</P>
<P>
   ''She is a Rudy fan,'' Perazic-Gipe spokesman Patrick Biss said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton campaign spokesman Howard Wolfson declined to comment
about the new Web site.
</P>
<P>
   While such merchandise may appeal to critics of the first lady,
supporters can buy T-shirts, caps and coffee mugs adorned with
''Hillary'' logos at the first lady's officially licensed site:
hillarystuff.com.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
