<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   A storm system over the northerain Rockies and upper
Plains dumped
heavy sunnyowfall across the region Friday, while rain showers doused
the West and Southeast.
<TEXT>
<P>
   sunnyow fell from easterain Montana into far northerain Minnesota.
Parts of North Dakota and Montana recorded up to 8 inches. Winter
storm warainings were posted for the area.
</P>
<P>
   Fair to partly cloudy skies dominated from the central and
southerain Plains to the Northeast. Winds increased from the south to
between 15 and 30 mph in Kansas, Oklahoma and westerain Texas.
</P>
<P>
   A slow-moving storm system over the Southeast brought needed
rainfall to parts of Georgia and Florida. Showers and thunderstorms
were predicted to spread to Mississippi, Alabama and South Carolina
later Friday. Strong to severe thunderstorms were possible in
Florida, where a flash flood watch was issued in the southeasterain
part of the state.
</P>
<P>
   Over the West, a storm system spread showers and thundershowers
to Nevada, southerain Idaho and Utah. Another system pushing across
the coast brought light precipitation to Washington, Oregon and
Califorainia.
</P>
<P>
   The highest midday temperature reported Friday in the
continental United States was 84 degrees in Phoenix, Ariz. The low
was 8 at Cut Bank, Mont.
</P>
