<HEADLINE> Boy Sues Over Teacher Relationship  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- A boy who fathered two children with his former
teacher has apparently decided he is a victim and is seeking
damages from a suburban municipality and school district.
</P>
<P>
   Vili Fualaau, 16, filed a claim against the municipality and
district where he became sexually involved with Mary Kay Letourneau
at the age of 12.
</P>
<P>
   Fualaau and his mother, Soona, say officials in south suburban
Des Moines and the Highline School District failed to protect him
from the sexual advances of a woman nearly three times his age.
Letourneau is serving a 7{-year sentence for child rape.
</P>
<P>
   In the past, Vili, his mother and Letourneau, 38, all
characterized the relationship as a love affair. Lawyers for the
boy and his family would not say whether there had been a
falling-out between Letourneau and the family.
</P>
<P>
   But the boy's lawyer, Cyrus R. Vance Jr., said Vili was too
immature to fully comprehend the relationship or the implications
of rearing two children.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was a very young boy,'' Vance said. ''He has two kids. It's
an oversimplification to conclude that he was having a mature love
affair.''
</P>
<P>
   Vance did not return a telephone call Friday seeking additional
comment on the boy's apparent change of heart.
</P>
<P>
   The claims seek damages that could exceed $1 million for
emotional suffering, lost income and the cost of rearing the girls,
who are being raised by Vili's mother.
</P>
<P>
   Lawyers for the municipality and school system say the claims
are without merit. If the claims remain unresolved by the end of
the month, the boy and his mother can sue in King County Superior
Court.
</P>
</TEXT>
