<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 22:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congo Leader Urges End To War  </HEADLINE>
By JAMES ANDERSON, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   HAVANA (AP) -- In an emotional speech at the Group of 77 summit,
Congo's foreign minister asked Third World leaders Friday to
pressure Rwanda, Uganda and Burundi to withdraw their forces from
his country.
</P>
<P>
   Breaking with the summit's theme of unity among poor nations
against rich nations, Abdoulaye Yerodia demanded that the summit
not ignore the 18 month old war in Congo.
</P>
<P>
   While not mentioning the countries by name, he said that at the
summit, three member nations had ignored the crisis in Central
Africa.
</P>
<P>
   ''No one has spoken about these things. They haven't even said
they are at war,'' Yerodia said.
</P>
<P>
   More than 1 million people have been displaced by fighting in
the Democratic Republic of Congo and the government has received
troops and arms from Zimbabwe, Angola and Namibia. The Congolese
government insists the rebel groups -- who also fight among
themselves -- are surrogates for Rwanda, Uganda and Burundi.
</P>
<P>
   ''They are part of the G-77. Do something to make these people
go home,'' he said. ''Stop their invasions so together we may turn
our eyes toward the North.''
</P>
<P>
   Rebels began fighting in 1998 to oust Congolese President
Laurent Kabila. Citing concerns about security along their common
borders, Rwanda, Burundi and Uganda supported the rebels.
</P>
<P>
   On Friday, a new cease-fire took effect in Congo. Yerodia
accused the rebels and their backers of already violating the
agreement.
</P>
<P>
   The U.N. Security Council plans to deploy a 5,500-strong U.N.
peacekeeping mission to monitor the disengagement within months.
</P>
<P>
   Yerodia noted that while summit speakers had emphasized
presenting a common front among developing nations, three G-77
nations were Congo's enemies.
</P>
<P>
   ''My brothers and sisters, where is OUR side?'' he declared. ''I
beg you to listen to what I'm saying. ... The aggressors should go
home.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-14-00 2243 </TRAILER>
