<HEADLINE> Brewers' Blanco Placed on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- The Brewers placed Henry Blanco on the 15-day
disabled list Friday with a lacerated right index finger.
</P>
<P>
   Blanco, acquired during the offseason from the Colorado Rockies
in a trade for Jeff Cirillo and Scott Karl, needed eight stitches
to close a cut between the first and second knuckle after a
collision at home plate.
</P>
<P>
   The Brewers, who released backup catchers Bobby Hughes and Brian
Banks during spring training, will call up Raul Casanova from
Triple-A Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
   Casanova was hitting .320 in six games with one home run and six
RBIs through Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   To make room for Casanova on the 40-man roster, the Brewers
moved pitcher Kyle Peterson to the 60-day DL. Peterson originally
was placed on the 15-day DL March 28 after surgery on his right
shoulder.
</P>
